threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Catch tsunami botnet based on string
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Sekoia.io

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a variant of the Tsunami (also known as Kaiten) IRC bot, a malicious tool used primarily for distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attacks. The binary implements a complete IRC-based command-and-control (C2) mechanism, parsed in the '._PRIVMSG' function. It contains multiple dedicated DDoS attack vectors: '.tsunami' (TCP flood), '.udp' (UDP flood), '.pan' (SYN/ACK flood), and '.unknown'. Additional malicious behaviors include the implementation of an 'identd' server for IRC authentication, IP spoofing capabilities through '.getspoof' and '.in_cksum', and the ability to execute remote shell commands via 'popen'. The bot also performs basic self-stealthing by clearing its process arguments (argv) in the 'main' function to hide its purpose from system monitoring tools.
